def: One who is born or bred in a city; a citizen. [Obs.] Champan.
A material for carpeting or floor covering, made of ground corkand caoutchouc or India rubber.
A genus of cruciferous plants (Alyssum) with white or yellowflowers and rounded pods. A. maritimum is the commonly cultivatedsweet alyssum, a fragrant white-flowered annual.
Having an acid quality; sour; acidulous. "With anxious,acidulent face." Carlyle.
A square; a measure; a rule. [Obs.] "With golden squire."Spenser.
Characterized by concinnity; neat; elegant. [R.]The most concinnous and most rotund of proffessors, M. Heyne. DeQuiency.
To satisfy the desire or appetite of; to satiate; to glut; tosurfeit.Crowds of wanderers sated with the business and pleasure of greatcities. Macaulay.
To cloud; to cover with mist; to dim. Shak.
By means of ocular view, or one's own observation. Sir T.Browne.
